text: Wulikare is a small settlement in Jubek State, South Sudan, about 0.5 km south of the Koda River, 4 km west of Ludo Kenyi, 14 km from the Jebel Lado mountain, 37 km southwest of Mongalla, and 29 km from the state capital Juba(2016): "South Sudan: Central equatoria - Base Map (as of 15 December 2016)". Médecins Sans Frontières. From the ReliefWeb.int site, accessed on 2019-03-24.(2013): "South Sudan: Central Equatoria State - Detailed Transport Map (as of 17 Jan 2013)". World Food Programme, Logistics Cluster. From the ReliefWeb.int site, accessed on 2019-03-24.Google Maps: "Wulikare". Accessed on 2019-03-24 It is located near on the road from Juba to Buko, Tijor, and Rokon.OpenStreetMap: "Wulikare". Accessed on 2019-03-24. ==References== Category:Populated places in Jubek State
title: Wulikare, South Sudan
